4 | Total\n!0||0||3||0||19||0||22||0\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=notes}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{FC Spartak Moscow}}\n{{2002 in Russian football}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2008 FC Spartak Moscow season}}\n[[Category:FC Spartak Moscow seasons]]\n[[Category:Russian football clubs 2002 season|Spartak Moscow]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club season\n| club               = [[FC Spartak Moscow|Spartak Moscow]]\n| season             = [[2002 in Russian football|2002]]\n| manager            = [[Oleg Romantsev]]\n| chairman           = \n| stadium            = [[Luzhniki Stadium]]\n| league             = [[2002 Russian Premier League|Premier League]]\n| league result      = 3rd\n| cup1               = [[2001\u201302 Russian Cup|Russian Cup]]\n| cup1 result        = ''Progressed to [[2003 FC Spartak Moscow|2003]] season''\n| cup2               = [[2002\u201303 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]]\n| cup2 result        = Group Stage\n| league topscorer   = [[Vladimir Beschastnykh]] (12)\n| season topscorer   = Vladimir Beschastnykh (14)\n| highest attendance = \n| lowest attendance  = \n| average attendance = \n| prevseason         = [[2001 FC Spartak Moscow season|2001]]\n| nextseason         = [[2003 FC Spartak Moscow season|2003]]\n}}\nThe '''2002 [[FC Spartak Moscow]] season''' was the clubs 11th season in the [[Russian Premier League]] season. Spartak were defending Premier League Champions, having won the previous six titles, but finished the season in third place. In the [[Russian Cup (football)|Russian Cup]], Spartak progressed the Quarterfinals of the [[2002\u201303 Russian Cup|2002\u201303]] cup, which will take place in the [[2003 FC Spartak Moscow|2003]] season. In Europe, Spartak finished bottom of their [[2002\u201303 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] group where they played [[Valencia CF|Valencia]], [[FC Basel|Basel]] and [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].\n\n==Squad==\n{{updated|match played 17 November 2002}}\n{