{"title_page": "Deep state in the United States", "text_new": "{{short description|Political terminology in the context of the US}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}{{Use American English|date=July 2019}}\n{{Politics of the United States}}\n\nIn the United States, the \"[[deep state]]\" is a [[conspiracy theory]]<ref>Barnes, Julian E.; Goldman, Adam; and Savage, Charlie (December 18, 2018) [https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/18/us/politics/deep-state-trump-classified-information.html \"Blaming the Deep State: Officials Accused of Wrongdoing Adopt Trump\u2019s Response\"] ''[[The New York Times]]''</ref><ref>Ruper, Aaron (June 17, 2019) [https://www.vox.com/2019/6/17/18681833/trump-stephanopoulos-fbi-obama-conspiracy-theory \"Trump accidentally undercuts his own \u201cdeep state\u201d FBI conspiracy theory\"] ''[[Vox Media|Vox]]''</ref><ref>Rothkopf, David (February 22, 2017) [https://foreignpolicy.com/2017/02/22/the-shallow-state-trump/ \"The Shallow State\"] ''[[Foreign Policy]]''</ref><ref>Jacobson, Zachary Jonathan (April 8, 2019) [https://www.washingtonpost.com/outlook/2019/04/08/how-paranoia-about-deep-state-brought-down-president/ \"How paranoia about the \u2018deep state\u2019 brought down a president\"] ''[[The Washington Post]]''</ref><ref>Blake, Aaron (March 28, 2019) [https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2019/03/28/trump-hannity-binge-conspiracy-theories-trumps-first-post-mueller-fox-news-interview \"Trump and Hannity binge on conspiracy theories in Trump\u2019s first post-Mueller Fox News interview\"] ''[[The Washington Post]]''</ref> which suggests that [[collusion]] and [[cronyism]] exist within the US political system and constitute a hidden government within the legitimately elected government.<ref name=stone>{{cite web|author=Hafford, Michael |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/deep-state-inside-donald-trumps-paranoid-conspiracy-theory-124236/ |title=Deep State: Inside Donald Trump's Paranoid Conspiracy Theory \u2013 Rolling Stone |publisher=Rollingstone.com |date=March 9, 2017|accessdate=May 29, 2019}}</ref><ref name=salon>{{cite web|url=https://www.salon.com/2017/03/09/the-alex-jones-influence-trumps-deep-state-fears-come-from-his-conspiracy-theorist-ally-and-adviser_partner/ |title=The Alex Jones influence: Trump's \"deep state\" fears come from his conspiracy theorist ally and adviser |publisher=Salon.com |date=March 10, 2017 |accessdate=May 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2018/apr/22/leaks-trump-deep-state-fbi-cia-michael-flynn|title=The 'deep state' is real. But are its leaks against Trump justified?|last=Goldsmith|first=Jack|date=April 22, 2018|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=October 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Osnos |first=Evan |title=Trump vs. the 'Deep State' |date=May 21, 2018 |url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2018/05/21/trump-vs-the-deep-state |work=The New Yorker| access-date=October 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Fallows |first1=James |authorlink= James Fallows|title=The Impending Senate Vote on Confirming Nominees |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2013/07/the-impending-senate-vote-on-confirming-nominees/277801/ |newspaper=[[The Atlantic Monthly]] |accessdate=October 21, 2018 |date=July 15, 2013}}</ref> Author [[Mike Lofgren]] believes that there is \"a hybrid association of elements of government and parts of top-level finance and industry that is effectively able to govern the United States without reference to the [[consent of the governed]] as expressed through the formal political process\",<ref name=\"Lofgren_2/21/2014\">{{cite web | last=Lofgren | first=Mike | title=Essay: Anatomy of the Deep State | website=[[BillMoyers.com]] | date=February 21, 2014 |url=https://billmoyers.com/2014/02/21/anatomy-of-the-deep-state/ | access-date=October 18, 2018}}</ref> or consider the deep state to encompass corruption prevalent among career politicians and civil servants.<ref name=\"Jessop\">{{cite book| last=Jessop|first=Bob|title=The State: Past, Present, Future|page=224|date=December 2015|publisher=John Wiley & Sons}}</ref>\n\nThe term was originally coined to refer to a relatively invisible state apparatus in [[Turkey]] \"composed of high-level elements within the intelligence services, military, security, judiciary, and organized crime\" and similar alleged networks in other countries including Egypt, Ukraine, Spain, Colombia, Italy, Israel, and many others.<ref name=Jessop/>\n\n== Definition ==\n{{Main|Deep state}}\nAccording to the journalist Robert Worth, \"the expression ''deep state'' had originated in Turkey in the 1990s, where the military colluded with [[drug trafficking|drug traffickers]] and hit men to wage a dirty war against Kurdish insurgents\".<ref>{{cite book|first=Robert F.|last=Worth|title=A Rage for Order: The Middle East in Turmoil, from Tahrir Square to ISIS|date=2016|publisher=Pan Macmillan|page=139|url=https://books.google.com/?id=PNOLCgAAQBAJ&pg=PP7&dq=rage+for+order+worth#v=onepage&q=rage%20for%20order%20worth&f=false|isbn=9780374710712}}</ref> The term \"deep state\" is likely a translation from the Turkish ''derin devlet'' (literally: \"deep state\" = \"deep polity\").<ref>[https://daily.jstor.org/the-unacknowledged-origins-of-the-deep-state/ \"The Turkish Origins of the \u201cDeep State\"], ''jstor.org'', April 10, 2017.</ref>\n\nIn ''The Concealment of the State'', Professor Jason Royce Lindsey argues that even without a conspiratorial agenda, the term ''deep state'' is useful for understanding aspects of the [[Military-industrial complex|national security establishment]] in developed countries, with emphasis on the United States. Lindsey writes that the deep state draws power from the national security and intelligence communities, a realm where secrecy is a source of power.<ref name=Lindsey>{{cite book| title=The Concealment of the State | first=Jason Royce | last= Lindsey | date=2013 | publisher=Bloomsbury | isbn=978-1-4411-7245-7 }}</ref>{{rp|35\u201336}} [[Alfred W. McCoy]] states that the increase in the power of the [[United States Intelligence Community|U.S. intelligence community]] since the [[September 11 attacks]] \"has built a fourth branch of the U.S. government\" that is \"in many ways autonomous from the executive, and increasingly so.\"<ref>{{cite web|authorlink=Jeremy Scahill|last=Scahill|first=Jeremy|url=https://theintercept.com/2017/07/22/donald-trump-and-the-coming-fall-of-american-empire/|title=Donald Trump and the Coming Fall of the American Empire|website=[[The Intercept]]|date=July 22, 2017|accessdate=July 29, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn a ''[[Foreign Affairs]]'' journal article and subsequent expansion in a law review, [[UCLA School of Law|UCLA Law]] professor Jon D. Michaels rejects \"the premise of an American deep state\u201d in a defense of what he terms the 'administrative state' against Trump's attempts to \u201cdeconstruct\" it. Michaels argues that the concept of the 'deep state' is more relevant to developing governments such as Egypt, Pakistan and [[Deep state in Turkey|Turkey]], \"where shadowy elites in the military and government ministries have been known to countermand or simply defy democratic directives\" than the United States \"where governmental power structures are almost entirely transparent\".<ref>{{cite magazine |first=Jon D. |last=Michaels |title=Trump and the 'Deep State' |magazine=Foreign Affairs |date=September\u2013October 2017|url=https://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/2017-08-15/trump-and-deep-state}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|first=Jon D. |last=Michaels |title=The American Deep State|journal=Notre Dame L. Rev. |volume=93 |page=1653 |date=2017 |url=https://scholarship.law.nd.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=4789&context=ndlr}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, former Democratic U.S. Representative [[Dennis Kucinich]] stated in an interview on Fox News that a deep state within the bureaucracy is trying to destroy Trump's presidency. He further elaborated \"The political process of the United States of America [is] under attack by intelligence agencies and individuals in those agencies...You have politicization of agencies that is resulting in leaks from anonymous, unknown people and the intention is to take down a president...Now this is very dangerous to America. It's a threat to our republic, it constitutes a clear and present danger to our way of life. So we have to be asking, what is the motive of these people? Who's putting these leaks out? Why doesn't somebody come forward and make a charge and put their name and reputation behind it, instead of attacking through the media and not substantiating their position?\" In an interview several months earlier Kucinich said \"What's at the core of this is an effort by some in the intelligence community to upend any positive relationship between the U.S. and Russia...There are people trying to separate the U.S. and Russia so this military-industrial-intel axis can cash in.\u201d<ref>https://www.salon.com/2017/02/16/is-michael-flynn-the-first-casualty-of-a-deep-state-coup-its-not-unthinkable</ref><ref>https://www.realclearpolitics.com/video/2017/05/18/kucinich_deep_state_trying_to_take_down_trump_our_country_is_under_attack_within.html</ref>\n\nAccording to [[David Gergen]], quoted in ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine, the term has been appropriated by [[Steve Bannon]] and ''[[Breitbart News]]'' and other supporters of the [[Presidency of Donald Trump|Trump Administration]] in order to delegitimize the critics of the current presidency.<ref name=\"Time\">{{cite journal|last1=Abramson|first1=Alana|title=President Trump's Allies Keep Talking About the 'Deep State'. What's That?|journal=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=March 8, 2017|url=http://time.com/4692178/donald-trump-deep-state-breitbart-barack-obama/|quote='This is a dark conspiratorial view that is being pushed by [top Trump strategist] Steve Bannon, his allies at Breitbart and some others in the conservative movement that is trying to delegitimize the opposition to Trump in many quarters and pass the blame to others,' said David Gergen.}}</ref> The 'deep state' theory has been dismissed by authors for ''[[The New York Times]]''<ref name=\"NY Times\">{{cite news|last1=Taub|first1=Amanda|last2=Fisher|first2=Max|title=As Leaks Multiply, Fears of a 'Deep State' in America|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/16/world/americas/deep-state-leaks-trump.html|work=The New York Times|date=February 16, 2017}}</ref> and ''[[New York Observer]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Schindler|first=John R.|url=http://observer.com/2017/02/donald-trump-administration-cia-deep-state/|title=Rebellion Brews in Washington\u2014But American 'Deep State' Is Only a Myth|work=New York Observer|date=February 22, 2017|accessdate=June 13, 2018}}</ref> [[University of Miami]] Professor [[Joseph Uscinski]] says, \"The concept has always been very popular among conspiracy theorists, whether they call it a deep state or something else.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=How the \"deep state\" conspiracy theory went mainstream|url=http://www.newsweek.com/deep-state-conspiracy-theory-trump-645376|accessdate=August 12, 2017|work=Newsweek|date=August 2, 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nFormer NSA leaker [[Edward Snowden]] has used the term generally to refer to the influence of [[United States federal civil service|civil servants]] over elected officials: \"the deep state is not just the intelligence agencies, it is really a way of referring to the career bureaucracy of government. These are officials who sit in powerful positions, who don't leave when presidents do, who watch presidents come and go&nbsp;... they influence policy, they influence presidents.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2018/03/19/news/snowden_how_the_deep_state_shapes_presidents_-191619170|title=Edward Snowden: 'Poisoning people who are long out of their service is contemptible'|date=March 18, 2018|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nIn an opinion piece by linguist [[Geoffrey Nunberg]], he said the \"deep state\" is an \"elastic label \u2013 depending on the occasion\" and its \"story conforms to the intricate grammar of those conspiracy narratives\". He also contrasted the change in the \"twin bogeys of conservative rhetoric\", from bureaucratic \"meddlesome bunglers\" of \"[[big government]]\" to \"conniving ideologues\" who \"orchestrates complex schemes\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2018/08/09/633019635/opinion-why-the-term-deep-state-speaks-to-conspiracy-theorists|title=Opinion: Why The Term 'Deep State' Speaks To Conspiracy Theorists|last=Nunberg|first=Geoff|work=NPR|access-date=August 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAccording to political scientist [[George Friedman]], the Deep State has been in place since 1871 and continues beneath the federal government, controlling and frequently reshaping policies; in this view the U.S. [[civil service]], was created to limit the power of the president. Prior to 1871, the president could select federal employees, all of whom served at the pleasure of the president. This is no longer the case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/the-deep-state_us_58c94a64e4b01d0d473bcfa3|title=The Deep State Is A Very Real Thing|last=Friedman|first=George|authorlink=George Friedman|date=March 15, 2017|website=[[The HuffingtonPost]]|publisher=|access-date=|quote=}}</ref>\n\nOn March 20, 2018, [[Rand Paul|Senator Rand Paul]] said \"Absolutely there is a deep state because the deep state is the intelligence communities that do not have oversight.\" He continued, \"There is ''no skeptic''\" [emphasis in original] among the four Republican and four Democratic Senators \"who are supposedly\" providing oversight, so that the intelligence communities, \"with their enormous power ... have become a deep state.\"<ref>{{cite podcast|url=http://admin.podcastone.com/episode/LI-Podcast-032018|title=Rand Paul: No question that there is a deep state|website=The Laura Ingraham Show|host=Laura Ingraham|date=March 20, 2018|time=30:19|access-date=December 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181206102310/http://admin.podcastone.com/episode/LI-Podcast-032018|archive-date=December 6, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> On December 4, 2018, Paul, in commenting on the CIA Director briefing only those eight Senators rather than the entire Senate, he added \"Do you want to know what the deep state is? The CIA Director is coming to the US Senate and only briefing a select few members of the Senate. Why shouldn\u2019t every senator know what is going on? The deep state wants to keep everyone in the dark. This is just ridiculous\"<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=RandPaul |author=Paul, Rand |number=1069969008030564353 |date = December 4, 2018 |title=Do you want to know what the deep state is?}}</ref> On December 10, 2018, he said \"The very definition of a 'deep state\u2019 is when the very people, congressional leaders \u2013 people who are elected by the people \u2013 are not allowed to hear the intelligence.\"<ref>{{cite interview |subject=Senator Rand Paul | title=Compares Exclusive C.I.A. Khashoggi Briefing to \u2018Deep State\u2019 |  |url=https://www.nytimes.com/video/us/politics/100000006246072/cia-khashoggi-briefing.html?action=click&contentCollection=timestopics\u00aeion=supplemental&module=undefined&contentPlacement=2&pgtype=collection |publisher=Associated Press |location=Washington, D.C |date=December 10, 2018 |work=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=December 10, 2018}}</ref>\n\nWriting in a piece for the ''[[Moyers & Company]]'' website, John Light asserts that the term deep state \"has been used for decades abroad to describe any network of entrenched government officials who function independently from elected politicians and work toward their own ends,\" but during the era of Trump the term has been twisted to mean \"a sub rosa part of the liberal establishment, that crowd resistant to the reality TV star\u2019s insurgent candidacy all along.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://billmoyers.com/story/the-deep-state-explained/|title=The Deep State, Explained|last=Light |first=John |date=March 31, 2017 |website=[[Moyers & Company]]|publisher=|access-date=July 6, 2019 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2020, Trump cabinet member and acting White House Chief of Staff [[Mick Mulvaney]], when asked if a deep state working against President Trump exists stated that it was \"absolutely 100% true\".<ref>https://www.businessinsider.com/mulvaney-says-deep-state-is-real-and-govt-officials-should-obey-trump-2020-2</ref>\n\n[[Michael Crowley (journalist)|Michael Crowley]], senior foreign affairs correspondent for ''[[Politico]]'' wrote, \"Beneath the politics of convenience is the reality that a large segment of the United States government really does operate without much transparency or public scrutiny, and has abused its awesome powers in myriad ways.\"<ref>[[Michael Crowley (journalist)|Crowley, Michael {September/October 2017) [https://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2017/09/05/deep-state-real-cia-fbi-intelligence-215537 \"The Deep State is Real: But it might not be what you think\"] ''[[Politico|Politico Magazine]]''</ref>\n\n== U.S. politics ==\n\nThe term \"deep state\" has been associated with the \"[[military\u2013industrial complex]]\" by several of the authors on the subject.<ref>{{cite web |title=\"Deep State\" in American History {{!}} C-SPAN.org |url=https://www.c-span.org/video/?461976-2/deep-state-american-history |website=www.c-span.org |language=en-us}}</ref> Potential risks from the military\u2013industrial complex were raised in President [[Dwight D. Eisenhower]]'s 1961 [[Eisenhower's farewell address|farewell address]]: \"In the councils of government, we must guard against the acquisition of unwarranted influence, whether sought or unsought, by the military\u2013industrial complex. The potential for the disastrous rise of misplaced power exists and will persist.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mcadams.posc.mu.edu/ike.htm|title=Eisenhower's Farewell Address to the Nation|website=mcadams.posc.mu.edu|access-date=August 9, 2017}}</ref> [[Stephen F. Cohen]] in his book ''War with Russia?'' (released November 27, 2018), claims that \"At least one U.S.\u2013Soviet summit seems to have been sabotaged. The third Eisenhower\u2013Khrushchev meeting, scheduled for Paris in 1960, was aborted by the Soviet shoot-down of a US U-2 spy plane sent, some think, by 'deep state' foes of detente.\"<ref>{{cite book |last=Cohen |first=Stephen F. |date=2019 |title=War with Russia? |url=|publisher=  Skyhorse Publishing, Inc. |page=190 |isbn=  978-1-5107-4581-0 }}</ref>\n\nMike Lofgren has claimed the military-industrial complex is the private part of the deep state.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mikelofgren.net/how-the-powers-that-be-maintain-the-deep-state/|title=\"Deep State\" Truthout Interview|date=February 22, 2016|access-date=August 9, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> However, [[Marc Ambinder]] has suggested that a myth about the \"deep state\" is that it functions as one entity; in reality, he states, \"the deep state contains multitudes, and they are often at odds with one another.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/five-myths-about-the-deep-state/2017/03/10/ddb09b54-04da-11e7-ad5b-d22680e18d10_story.html|title=Five myths about the deep state|last=Ambinder|first=Marc|date=March 10, 2017|work=The Washington Post|access-date=August 9, 2017|last2=Ambinder|first2=Marc|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref>\n\n[[Tufts University]] professor [[Michael J. Glennon]] claimed that President [[Barack Obama]] did not succeed in resisting and/or changing what he calls the \"double government\": the defense and national security network.<ref>{{Cite news|author=Smith, Jordan Michael|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/ideas/2014/10/18/vote-all-you-want-the-secret-government-won-change/jVSkXrENQlu8vNcBfMn9sL/story.html|title=Vote all you want. The secret government won't change.| newspaper=[[Boston Globe]]|date=October 18, 2014|access-date=August 22, 2017}}</ref> Mike Lofgren felt Obama was pushed into the [[War in Afghanistan (2001\u2013present)#2009 Increase in U.S. troops|Afghanistan \"surge\" in 2009]].<ref name=\"Lofgren_2/21/2014\"/> Another major campaign promise Obama made was the closure of [[Guantanamo Bay detention camp|Guantanamo Bay Prison Camp]], which he was unable to accomplish. This has been attributed indirectly to the influence of a deep state.<ref name=\"Time\" />\n\nPresident Donald Trump's supporters use the term to refer to allegations that intelligence officers and [[United States Executive Branch|executive branch]] officials guide policy through [[news leak|leaking]] or other internal means.<ref name=\"WaPo Ishaan\">{{Cite news |title=Is Trump fighting the deep state or creating his own? |author=Tharoor, Ishaan |date=February 1, 2017 |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/worldviews/wp/2017/02/01/is-trump-fighting-the-deep-state-or-creating-his-own/ }}</ref><ref name=\"NY Times\" /> According to a July 2017 report by the [[United States Senate Committee on Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs]], \"the Trump administration was being hit by national security leaks 'on a nearly daily basis' and at a far higher rate than its predecessors encountered\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Crowley|first=Michael|url=http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2017/09/05/deep-state-real-cia-fbi-intelligence-215537|title=The Deep State Is Real|website=[[Politico Magazine]]|date=September\u2013October 2017|accessdate=September 5, 2017}}</ref>\n\nTrump and [[Steve Bannon]], his former chief strategist, have both made allegations about a deep state which they believe is interfering with the president's agenda.<ref name=\"Times Bannon\">{{Cite news |title=Rumblings of a 'Deep State' Undermining Trump? It Was Once a Foreign Concept |author= Davis, Julie Hirschfeld |date=March 6, 2017 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/06/us/politics/deep-state-trump.html }}</ref><ref name=\"WaPo Bannon\">{{Cite news |title=Inside Trump's fury: The president rages at leaks, setbacks and accusations |author=Rucker, Phillip; Costa, Robert; and Parker, Ashley|date=March 5, 2017 |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/inside-trumps-fury-the-president-rages-at-leaks-setbacks-and-accusations/2017/03/05/40713af4-01df-11e7-ad5b-d22680e18d10_story.html }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Winter|first1=Jana|last2=Groll|first2=Elias|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2017/08/10/heres-the-memo-that-blew-up-the-nsc/|title=Here's the Memo That Blew Up the NSC|website=[[Foreign Policy]]|date=August 10, 2017|accessdate=August 15, 2017}}</ref> In 2018, describing the deep state as an \"entrenched bureaucracy\", Trump accused the [[United States Department of Justice]] \"of being part of the 'deep state{{'\"}} in a statement advocating the prosecution of [[Huma Abedin]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lucey|first1=Catherine|last2=Superville|first2=Darlene|url=https://apnews.com/8720fde079e84237b8e6cca4219aafb2/Trump-accuses-DOJ-of-being-part-of-'deep-state'|title=Trump accuses DOJ of being part of 'deep state'|website=[[Associated Press]]|date=January 2, 2018|accessdate=January 2, 2018}}</ref> Some Trump allies and right-wing media outlets have alleged that former president Barack Obama is coordinating a deep state resistance to Trump.<ref name=\"Times Bannon\" /><ref name=\"Wapo Obama\">{{Cite news |title=Trump and Republicans see a 'deep state' foe: Barack Obama |author= Weigel, David|date=March 7, 2017 |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/powerpost/wp/2017/03/07/trump-and-republicans-see-a-deep-state-foe-barack-obama/ }}</ref> While the belief in a deep state is popular among Trump supporters, critics maintain that it has no basis in reality,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://thehill.com/homenews/administration/336178-the-memo-is-trump-a-victim-of-the-deep-state|title=THE MEMO: Is Trump a victim of the 'deep state'?|newspaper=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]|date=June 5, 2017|first=Niall|last=Stanage}}</ref> arguing that the sources of the leaks frustrating the Trump administration lack the organizational depth of deep states in other countries. Critics also warned that use of the term in the U.S. could undermine confidence in vital institutions and be used to justify suppressing dissent.<ref name=\"Times Bannon\" /><ref name=\"Atlantic dangerous\">{{Cite news |title=Why it's dangerous to talk about a deep state |author=Graham, David A.|date=February 20, 2017 |newspaper=[[The Atlantic Monthly]]|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2017/02/why-its-dangerous-to-talk-about-a-deep-state/517221/ }}</ref>\n\n''[[The Washington Post]]'''s long-time conservative columnist, [[Charles Krauthammer]] said of the belief in a Deep State:\n\n<blockquote>I don\u2019t believe in the tooth fairy, the [[Knights Templar]], [[Bilderberg Group|Bilderberg]], the [[Protocols of the Elders of Zion]], a vast right wing conspiracy, or, for that matter, a vast left wing conspiracy. Are there in the U.S. government individual bureaucrats that are Democratic holdovers that would love nothing more than to damage Trump? Yeah, of course there are. Is there a concealed web of conspirators, malevolent permanent hidden shadow government? Rubbish. And I would add that Lee Harvey Oswald acted alone without the help of Ted Cruz\u2019s father.<ref name=stone /></blockquote>\n\n''[[Rolling Stone]]'' magazine, which reported Krauthammer's comment, summarizes the Deep State concept this way: \"Is there actually a deep state? If you mean entrenched bureaucracy, then of course there is. If you mean a government-wide conspiracy, then the answer is almost certainly no.\"<ref name=stone /> ''[[Salon (magazine)|Salon]]'' magazine traces Donald Trump's belief in a Deep State to [[conspiracy theorist]] [[Alex Jones]] of ''[[Infowars]]'', who, it says, \"believes that the government \u2014 a.k.a. the \"deep state\" \u2014 has orchestrated attacks and events throughout history. This includes the [[Oklahoma City bombing|bombing of the Oklahoma City federal building]], the [[Sandy Hook Elementary School shooting|massacre at Sandy Hook]] (he claims that many of the parents were actors), the [[Boston Marathon bombing|Boston Marathon attack]], and on and on,\" including believing that the [[9/11 conspiracy theories|9/11 attack]] was \"executed by the United States government.\" The magazine also points to Trump's long-time ally, [[Roger Stone]], as an influence. Stone has written several books which center on conspiracy theories, and blames [[Lyndon B. Johnson|Lyndon Johnson]] for the death of President [[John F. Kennedy]], and that Ted Cruz's father was involved in that assassination.<ref name=salon />\n\nIn an article for ''[[The New York Review of Books]]'', [[Michael Tomasky]] quoted [[Newt Gingrich]] as using the term in the context of the [[Robert Mueller]] investigation in July 2018, quoting Gingrich stating: \"[Mueller is] ... the tip of the deep state spear aimed at destroying or at a minimum undermining and crippling the Trump presidency\".<ref name=\"auto\">''The New York Review of Books'', Michael Tomalsky, August 16, 2018. Page 8.</ref> Gingrich then added to the statement that: \"The brazen redefinition of Mueller's task tells you how arrogant the deep state is and how confident it is it can get away with anything\".<ref name=\"auto\" />\n\nProfessor of international relations at Harvard University, [[Stephen Walt]], has written: \"There's no secret conspiracy or deep state running U.S. foreign policy; to the extent that there is a bipartisan foreign-policy elite, it is hiding in plain sight.\"<ref name=\"Walt_9/7/2018\">{{cite web | last=Walt | first=Stephen M. | title=The Battle for Crazytown | website=[[Foreign Policy]] | date=September 7, 2018 |url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2018/09/07/the-battle-for-crazytown/ | access-date=October 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe term has also been used in comments on the \"deep state\"-like influence allegedly wielded by career military officers such as [[H. R. McMaster]], [[John F. Kelly|John Kelly]] and [[James Mattis]] in the Trump administration. The anthropologist C. August Elliott described this state of affairs as the emergence of a 'shallow state': \"an America where public servants now function as tugboats guiding the President's very leaky ship through the shallows and away from a potential shipwreck\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Elliott |first1=C. August |title=MOABs win battles but they don't win wars |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-04-15/moabs-win-battles-but-they-dont-win-wars/8445710 |website=ABC News |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation}}</ref>\n\nOn September 5, 2018, ''[[The New York Times]]'' published an anonymous op-ed titled \"[[I Am Part of the Resistance Inside the Trump Administration]]\" written by a \"senior official in the Trump Administration\". In the essay, the official was critical of President Trump and claimed \"that many of the senior officials in [Trump's] own administration are working diligently from within to frustrate parts of his agenda and his worst inclinations\".<ref>{{cite news |author1=Anonymous |title=I Am Part of the Resistance Inside the Trump Administration |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/05/opinion/trump-white-house-anonymous-resistance.html |newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=November 17, 2018 |date=September 5, 2018}}</ref> [[House Majority Leader]] [[Kevin McCarthy (California politician)|Kevin McCarthy]] described this as evidence of the deep state at work,<ref>{{cite news |last1=McCarthy |first1=Kevin |title=A Top Republican Fires Back at 'Anonymous' |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/07/opinion/letters/kevin-mccarthy-trump-anonymous.html |website=The New York Times |accessdate=November 17, 2018 |date=September 7, 2018}}</ref> and [[David Bossie]] wrote an op-ed at Fox News claiming this was the deep state \"working against the will of the American people\".<ref name=\"7 September 2018\">{{cite web |last1=Bossie |first1=David N. |title=Anonymous NY Times op-ed shows Deep State thugs are working against the will of the American people|url=https://www.foxnews.com/opinion/anonymous-ny-times-op-ed-shows-deep-state-thugs-are-working-against-the-will-of-the-american-people.amp |newspaper=[[Fox News]] |accessdate=November 17, 2018}}</ref> However, there was some doubt as to the actual importance of the anonymous author with some estimating hundreds or thousands of possible positions could be considered \"senior officials\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Concha |first1=Joe |title='Senior' official doesn't mean anonymous NYT writer is close to Trump |url=https://thehill.com/opinion/white-house/405323-senior-official-doesnt-mean-anonymous-nyt-writer-is-close-to-trump?amp |website=The Hill |accessdate=November 17, 2018 |date=September 6, 2018}}</ref> and the inherent paradox of exposing the existence of such a group.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chait |first1=Jonathan |title=Senior White House Official Confesses Anti-Trump Cabal in Newspaper Trump Reads |url=http://nymag.com/intelligencer/amp/2018/09/senior-white-house-official-confesses-anti-trump-cabal.html |website=Intelligencer |accessdate= November 17, 2018 |date=September 5, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Polls ==\nAccording to a poll of Americans in April 2017, about half (48%) thought there was a \"deep state\", defined as \"military, intelligence and government officials who try to secretly manipulate government\", while about a third (35%) of all participants thought it was a conspiracy theory and the remainder (17%) had no opinion. Of those who believe a \"deep state\" exists, more than half (58%) said it was a major problem, a net of 28% of those surveyed.<ref name=\"ABC_47032061\">{{cite news|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/lies-damn-lies-deep-state-plenty-americans-poll/story?id=47032061|title=Nearly half of Americans think there's a 'deep state' in US: Poll|author= Staff|date=April 27, 2017|newspaper=[[ABC News]]|access-date=March 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.langerresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/1186a4DeepStateFakeNews.pdf|title=Lies, Damn Lies and the Deep State: Plenty of Americans See Them All|author=Langer Research Associates|publisher=[[ABC News]]}}</ref>\n\nA March 2018 poll found most respondents (63%) were unfamiliar with the term \"deep state\", but a majority believe that a deep state likely exists in the United States when described as \"a group of unelected government and military officials who secretly manipulate or direct national policy\". Three-fourths (74%) of the respondents say that they believe this type of group definitely (27%) or probably (47%) exists in the federal government.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/03/19/politics/americans-skeptical-government-poll/index.html|title=Americans skeptical of government, more politically engaged, poll finds|author=Wright, avid|newspaper=[[CNN]]|access-date=March 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Morin, Rebecca|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/03/19/poll-deep-state-470282||title=Poll: Majority believe 'deep state' manipulates U.S. policies|newspaper=[[Politico]]|access-date=March 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Staff|url=https://www.monmouth.edu/polling-institute/reports/monmouthpoll_us_031918|title=Public Troubled by 'Deep State'|work=[[Monmouth University Polling Institute]]|access-date=March 23, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAn October 2019 [[The Economist]]/[[YouGov]] poll found that, without giving a definition of \"deep state\" to respondents, 70% of Republicans, 38% of independents, and 13% of Democrats agreed that a \"deep state\" was \"trying to overthrow Trump.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://today.yougov.com/topics/politics/articles-reports/2019/10/16/americans-favor-impeachment-want-trump-removed|title=Americans who favor impeachment want President Trump removed, too {{!}} YouGov|last=Frankovic|first=Kathy|website=today.yougov.com|language=en-us|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref>\n\n==Closely related concepts==\nBob Jessop, in his book ''The State: Past, Present, Future'',<ref name=\"Jessop\"/> notes the similarity of three constructs:\n# 'Deep state' \u2013 for which he cites Mike Lofgren's 2014 definition: \"a hybrid association of elements of government and parts of top-level finance and industry that is effectively able to govern&nbsp;... without reference to the consent of the governed as expressed through the formal political process\".<ref name=\"Lofgren_2/21/2014\"/>\n# 'Dark state' \u2013 \"networks of officials, private firms, media outlets, think tanks, foundations, NGOs, interest groups, and other forces that attend to the needs of capital, not of everyday life\" while \"concealed from public gaze\" (or \"hidden in plain sight\"), citing Jason Lindsay (2013).{{verify quote|date=February 2019}}<ref name=Lindsey/>{{rp|37\u201338}}\n# '[[Fourth branch of government|The Fourth Branch]]' of US government \u2013 consisting of \"an ever more unchecked and unaccountable centre&nbsp;..., working behind a veil of secrecy\", citing Tom Engelhardt (2014).<ref>{{cite book | first= Tom | last=Engelhardt | title = Shadow Government: Surveillance, Secret Wars, and a Global Security State in a Single Superpower World | date=2014 | publisher= Haymarket Books | location=Chicago | isbn=9781608464272}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{col-begin|width=60%}}{{col-break}}\n* [[Bureaucracy]]\n* [[Bureaucrat]]\n* [[Council for National Policy]]\n* [[Coup d'\u00e9tat]]\n* [[Deep state in Turkey]]\n* [[Fourth branch of government]]\n* [[Groundswell group]]\n* [[Iron triangle (US politics)]]\n{{col-break}}\n* \"[[I Am Part of the Resistance Inside the Trump Administration]]\"\n* [[Military\u2013industrial complex]]\n* [[National security|National security state]]\n* [[QAnon]]\n* [[Shadow government (conspiracy)]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{cite book|author=James B. Stewart |authorlink=James B. Stewart |title=Deep State: Trump, the FBI, and the Rule of Law |publisher=[[Penguin Press]] |year=2019 |isbn=978-0525559108 |url=}}\n\n[[Category:Conspiracy theories in the United States]]\n[[Category:Conspiracy theories promoted by Donald Trump]]\n[[Category:Corruption in the United States]]\n[[Category:Deep politics]]\n[[Category:Political terminology of the United States]]\n[[Category:Political geography]]\n[[Category:Politics of the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Political terminology in the context of the US}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}{{Use American English|date=July 2019}}\n{{Politics of the United States}}\n\nIn the United States, the \"[[deep state]]\" is a [[conspiracy theory]]<ref>Barnes, Julian E.; Goldman, Adam; and Savage, Charlie (December 18, 2018) [https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/18/us/politics/deep-state-trump-classified-information.html \"Blaming the Deep State: Officials Accused of Wrongdoing Adopt Trump\u2019s Response\"] ''[[The New York Times]]''</ref><ref>Ruper, Aaron (June 17, 2019) [https://www.vox.com/2019/6/17/18681833/trump-stephanopoulos-fbi-obama-conspiracy-theory \"Trump accidentally undercuts his own \u201cdeep state\u201d FBI conspiracy theory\"] ''[[Vox Media|Vox]]''</ref><ref>Rothkopf, David (February 22, 2017) [https://foreignpolicy.com/2017/02/22/the-shallow-state-trump/ \"The Shallow State\"] ''[[Foreign Policy]]''</ref><ref>Jacobson, Zachary Jonathan (April 8, 2019) [https://www.washingtonpost.com/outlook/2019/04/08/how-paranoia-about-deep-state-brought-down-president/ \"How paranoia about the \u2018deep state\u2019 brought down a president\"] ''[[The Washington Post]]''</ref><ref>Blake, Aaron (March 28, 2019) [https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2019/03/28/trump-hannity-binge-conspiracy-theories-trumps-first-post-mueller-fox-news-interview \"Trump and Hannity binge on conspiracy theories in Trump\u2019s first post-Mueller Fox News interview\"] ''[[The Washington Post]]''</ref> which suggests that [[collusion]] and [[cronyism]] exist within the US political system and constitute a hidden government within the legitimately elected government.<ref name=stone>{{cite web|author=Hafford, Michael |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/deep-state-inside-donald-trumps-paranoid-conspiracy-theory-124236/ |title=Deep State: Inside Donald Trump's Paranoid Conspiracy Theory \u2013 Rolling Stone |publisher=Rollingstone.com |date=March 9, 2017|accessdate=May 29, 2019}}</ref><ref name=salon>{{cite web|url=https://www.salon.com/2017/03/09/the-alex-jones-influence-trumps-deep-state-fears-come-from-his-conspiracy-theorist-ally-and-adviser_partner/ |title=The Alex Jones influence: Trump's \"deep state\" fears come from his conspiracy theorist ally and adviser |publisher=Salon.com |date=March 10, 2017 |accessdate=May 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2018/apr/22/leaks-trump-deep-state-fbi-cia-michael-flynn|title=The 'deep state' is real. But are its leaks against Trump justified?|last=Goldsmith|first=Jack|date=April 22, 2018|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=October 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Osnos |first=Evan |title=Trump vs. the 'Deep State' |date=May 21, 2018 |url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2018/05/21/trump-vs-the-deep-state |work=The New Yorker| access-date=October 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Fallows |first1=James |authorlink= James Fallows|title=The Impending Senate Vote on Confirming Nominees |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2013/07/the-impending-senate-vote-on-confirming-nominees/277801/ |newspaper=[[The Atlantic Monthly]] |accessdate=October 21, 2018 |date=July 15, 2013}}</ref> Author [[Mike Lofgren]] believes that there is \"a hybrid association of elements of government and parts of top-level finance and industry that is effectively able to govern the United States without reference to the [[consent of the governed]] as expressed through the formal political process\",<ref name=\"Lofgren_2/21/2014\">{{cite web | last=Lofgren | first=Mike | title=Essay: Anatomy of the Deep State | website=[[BillMoyers.com]] | date=February 21, 2014 |url=https://billmoyers.com/2014/02/21/anatomy-of-the-deep-state/ | access-date=October 18, 2018}}</ref> or consider the deep state to encompass corruption prevalent among career politicians and civil servants.<ref name=\"Jessop\">{{cite book| last=Jessop|first=Bob|title=The State: Past, Present, Future|page=224|date=December 2015|publisher=John Wiley & Sons}}</ref>\n\nThe term was originally coined to refer to a relatively invisible state apparatus in [[Turkey]] \"composed of high-level elements within the intelligence services, military, security, judiciary, and organized crime\" and similar alleged networks in other countries including Egypt, Ukraine, Spain, Colombia, Italy, Israel, and many others.<ref name=Jessop/>\n\n== Definition ==\n{{Main|Deep state}}\nAccording to the journalist Robert Worth, \"the expression ''deep state'' had originated in Turkey in the 1990s, where the military colluded with [[drug trafficking|drug traffickers]] and hit men to wage a dirty war against Kurdish insurgents\".<ref>{{cite book|first=Robert F.|last=Worth|title=A Rage for Order: The Middle East in Turmoil, from Tahrir Square to ISIS|date=2016|publisher=Pan Macmillan|page=139|url=https://books.google.com/?id=PNOLCgAAQBAJ&pg=PP7&dq=rage+for+order+worth#v=onepage&q=rage%20for%20order%20worth&f=false|isbn=9780374710712}}</ref> The term \"deep state\" is likely a translation from the Turkish ''derin devlet'' (literally: \"deep state\" = \"deep polity\").<ref>[https://daily.jstor.org/the-unacknowledged-origins-of-the-deep-state/ \"The Turkish Origins of the \u201cDeep State\"], ''jstor.org'', April 10, 2017.</ref>\n\nIn ''The Concealment of the State'', Professor Jason Royce Lindsey argues that even without a conspiratorial agenda, the term ''deep state'' is useful for understanding aspects of the [[Military-industrial complex|national security establishment]] in developed countries, with emphasis on the United States. Lindsey writes that the deep state draws power from the national security and intelligence communities, a realm where secrecy is a source of power.<ref name=Lindsey>{{cite book| title=The Concealment of the State | first=Jason Royce | last= Lindsey | date=2013 | publisher=Bloomsbury | isbn=978-1-4411-7245-7 }}</ref>{{rp|35\u201336}} [[Alfred W. McCoy]] states that the increase in the power of the [[United States Intelligence Community|U.S. intelligence community]] since the [[September 11 attacks]] \"has built a fourth branch of the U.S. government\" that is \"in many ways autonomous from the executive, and increasingly so.\"<ref>{{cite web|authorlink=Jeremy Scahill|last=Scahill|first=Jeremy|url=https://theintercept.com/2017/07/22/donald-trump-and-the-coming-fall-of-american-empire/|title=Donald Trump and the Coming Fall of the American Empire|website=[[The Intercept]]|date=July 22, 2017|accessdate=July 29, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn a ''[[Foreign Affairs]]'' journal article and subsequent expansion in a law review, [[UCLA School of Law|UCLA Law]] professor Jon D. Michaels rejects \"the premise of an American deep state\u201d in a defense of what he terms the 'administrative state' against Trump's attempts to \u201cdeconstruct\" it. Michaels argues that the concept of the 'deep state' is more relevant to developing governments such as Egypt, Pakistan and [[Deep state in Turkey|Turkey]], \"where shadowy elites in the military and government ministries have been known to countermand or simply defy democratic directives\" than the United States \"where governmental power structures are almost entirely transparent\".<ref>{{cite magazine |first=Jon D. |last=Michaels |title=Trump and the 'Deep State' |magazine=Foreign Affairs |date=September\u2013October 2017|url=https://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/2017-08-15/trump-and-deep-state}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|first=Jon D. |last=Michaels |title=The American Deep State|journal=Notre Dame L. Rev. |volume=93 |page=1653 |date=2017 |url=https://scholarship.law.nd.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=4789&context=ndlr}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, former Democratic U.S. Representative [[Dennis Kucinich]] stated in an interview on Fox News that a deep state within the bureaucracy is trying to destroy Trump's presidency. He further elaborated \"The political process of the United States of America [is] under attack by intelligence agencies and individuals in those agencies...You have politicization of agencies that is resulting in leaks from anonymous, unknown people and the intention is to take down a president...Now this is very dangerous to America. It's a threat to our republic, it constitutes a clear and present danger to our way of life. So we have to be asking, what is the motive of these people? Who's putting these leaks out? Why doesn't somebody come forward and make a charge and put their name and reputation behind it, instead of attacking through the media and not substantiating their position?\" In an interview several months earlier Kucinich said \"What's at the core of this is an effort by some in the intelligence community to upend any positive relationship between the U.S. and Russia...There are people trying to separate the U.S. and Russia so this military-industrial-intel axis can cash in.\u201d<ref>https://www.salon.com/2017/02/16/is-michael-flynn-the-first-casualty-of-a-deep-state-coup-its-not-unthinkable</ref><ref>https://www.realclearpolitics.com/video/2017/05/18/kucinich_deep_state_trying_to_take_down_trump_our_country_is_under_attack_within.html</ref>\n\nAccording to [[David Gergen]], quoted in ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine, the term has been appropriated by [[Steve Bannon]] and ''[[Breitbart News]]'' and other supporters of the [[Presidency of Donald Trump|Trump Administration]] in order to delegitimize the critics of the current presidency.<ref name=\"Time\">{{cite journal|last1=Abramson|first1=Alana|title=President Trump's Allies Keep Talking About the 'Deep State'. What's That?|journal=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=March 8, 2017|url=http://time.com/4692178/donald-trump-deep-state-breitbart-barack-obama/|quote='This is a dark conspiratorial view that is being pushed by [top Trump strategist] Steve Bannon, his allies at Breitbart and some others in the conservative movement that is trying to delegitimize the opposition to Trump in many quarters and pass the blame to others,' said David Gergen.}}</ref> The 'deep state' theory has been dismissed by authors for ''[[The New York Times]]''<ref name=\"NY Times\">{{cite news|last1=Taub|first1=Amanda|last2=Fisher|first2=Max|title=As Leaks Multiply, Fears of a 'Deep State' in America|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/16/world/americas/deep-state-leaks-trump.html|work=The New York Times|date=February 16, 2017}}</ref> and ''[[New York Observer]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Schindler|first=John R.|url=http://observer.com/2017/02/donald-trump-administration-cia-deep-state/|title=Rebellion Brews in Washington\u2014But American 'Deep State' Is Only a Myth|work=New York Observer|date=February 22, 2017|accessdate=June 13, 2018}}</ref> [[University of Miami]] Professor [[Joseph Uscinski]] says, \"The concept has always been very popular among conspiracy theorists, whether they call it a deep state or something else.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=How the \"deep state\" conspiracy theory went mainstream|url=http://www.newsweek.com/deep-state-conspiracy-theory-trump-645376|accessdate=August 12, 2017|work=Newsweek|date=August 2, 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nFormer NSA leaker [[Edward Snowden]] has used the term generally to refer to the influence of [[United States federal civil service|civil servants]] over elected officials: \"the deep state is not just the intelligence agencies, it is really a way of referring to the career bureaucracy of government. These are officials who sit in powerful positions, who don't leave when presidents do, who watch presidents come and go&nbsp;... they influence policy, they influence presidents.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2018/03/19/news/snowden_how_the_deep_state_shapes_presidents_-191619170|title=Edward Snowden: 'Poisoning people who are long out of their service is contemptible'|date=March 18, 2018|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nIn an opinion piece by linguist [[Geoffrey Nunberg]], he said the \"deep state\" is an \"elastic label \u2013 depending on the occasion\" and its \"story conforms to the intricate grammar of those conspiracy narratives\". He also contrasted the change in the \"twin bogeys of conservative rhetoric\", from bureaucratic \"meddlesome bunglers\" of \"[[big government]]\" to \"conniving ideologues\" who \"orchestrates complex schemes\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2018/08/09/633019635/opinion-why-the-term-deep-state-speaks-to-conspiracy-theorists|title=Opinion: Why The Term 'Deep State' Speaks To Conspiracy Theorists|last=Nunberg|first=Geoff|work=NPR|access-date=August 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAccording to political scientist [[George Friedman]], the Deep State has been in place since 1871 and continues beneath the federal government, controlling and frequently reshaping policies; in this view the U.S. [[civil service]], was created to limit the power of the president. Prior to 1871, the president could select federal employees, all of whom served at the pleasure of the president. This is no longer the case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/the-deep-state_us_58c94a64e4b01d0d473bcfa3|title=The Deep State Is A Very Real Thing|last=Friedman|first=George|authorlink=George Friedman|date=March 15, 2017|website=[[The HuffingtonPost]]|publisher=|access-date=|quote=}}</ref>\n\nOn March 20, 2018, [[Rand Paul|Senator Rand Paul]] said \"Absolutely there is a deep state because the deep state is the intelligence communities that do not have oversight.\" He continued, \"There is ''no skeptic''\" [emphasis in original] among the four Republican and four Democratic Senators \"who are supposedly\" providing oversight, so that the intelligence communities, \"with their enormous power ... have become a deep state.\"<ref>{{cite podcast|url=http://admin.podcastone.com/episode/LI-Podcast-032018|title=Rand Paul: No question that there is a deep state|website=The Laura Ingraham Show|host=Laura Ingraham|date=March 20, 2018|time=30:19|access-date=December 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181206102310/http://admin.podcastone.com/episode/LI-Podcast-032018|archive-date=December 6, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> On December 4, 2018, Paul, in commenting on the CIA Director briefing only those eight Senators rather than the entire Senate, he added \"Do you want to know what the deep state is? The CIA Director is coming to the US Senate and only briefing a select few members of the Senate. Why shouldn\u2019t every senator know what is going on? The deep state wants to keep everyone in the dark. This is just ridiculous\"<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=RandPaul |author=Paul, Rand |number=1069969008030564353 |date = December 4, 2018 |title=Do you want to know what the deep state is?}}</ref> On December 10, 2018, he said \"The very definition of a 'deep state\u2019 is when the very people, congressional leaders \u2013 people who are elected by the people \u2013 are not allowed to hear the intelligence.\"<ref>{{cite interview |subject=Senator Rand Paul | title=Compares Exclusive C.I.A. Khashoggi Briefing to \u2018Deep State\u2019 |  |url=https://www.nytimes.com/video/us/politics/100000006246072/cia-khashoggi-briefing.html?action=click&contentCollection=timestopics\u00aeion=supplemental&module=undefined&contentPlacement=2&pgtype=collection |publisher=Associated Press |location=Washington, D.C |date=December 10, 2018 |work=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=December 10, 2018}}</ref>\n\nWriting in a piece for the ''[[Moyers & Company]]'' website, John Light asserts that the term deep state \"has been used for decades abroad to describe any network of entrenched government officials who function independently from elected politicians and work toward their own ends,\" but during the era of Trump the term has been twisted to mean \"a sub rosa part of the liberal establishment, that crowd resistant to the reality TV star\u2019s insurgent candidacy all along.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://billmoyers.com/story/the-deep-state-explained/|title=The Deep State, Explained|last=Light |first=John |date=March 31, 2017 |website=[[Moyers & Company]]|publisher=|access-date=July 6, 2019 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2020, Trump cabinet member and acting White House Chief of Staff [[Mick Mulvaney]], when asked if a deep state working against President Trump exists stated that it was \"absolutely 100% true\".<ref>https://www.businessinsider.com/mulvaney-says-deep-state-is-real-and-govt-officials-should-obey-trump-2020-2</ref>\n\n[[Michael Crowley (journalist)|Michael Crowley]], senior foreign affairs correspondent for ''[[Politico]]'' wrote, \"Beneath the politics of convenience is the reality that a large segment of the United States government really does operate without much transparency or public scrutiny, and has abused its awesome powers in myriad ways.\"<ref>[[Michael Crowley (journalist)|Crowley, Michael {September/October 2017) [https://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2017/09/05/deep-state-real-cia-fbi-intelligence-215537 \"The Deep State is Real: But it might not be what you think\"] ''[[Politico|Politico Magazine]]''</ref>\n\n== U.S. politics ==\n\nThe term \"deep state\" has been associated with the \"[[military\u2013industrial complex]]\" by several of the authors on the subject.<ref>{{cite web |title=\"Deep State\" in American History {{!}} C-SPAN.org |url=https://www.c-span.org/video/?461976-2/deep-state-american-history |website=www.c-span.org |language=en-us}}</ref> Potential risks from the military\u2013industrial complex were raised in President [[Dwight D. Eisenhower]]'s 1961 [[Eisenhower's farewell address|farewell address]]: \"In the councils of government, we must guard against the acquisition of unwarranted influence, whether sought or unsought, by the military\u2013industrial complex. The potential for the disastrous rise of misplaced power exists and will persist.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mcadams.posc.mu.edu/ike.htm|title=Eisenhower's Farewell Address to the Nation|website=mcadams.posc.mu.edu|access-date=August 9, 2017}}</ref> [[Stephen F. Cohen]] in his book ''War with Russia?'' (released November 27, 2018), claims that \"At least one U.S.\u2013Soviet summit seems to have been sabotaged. The third Eisenhower\u2013Khrushchev meeting, scheduled for Paris in 1960, was aborted by the Soviet shoot-down of a US U-2 spy plane sent, some think, by 'deep state' foes of detente.\"<ref>{{cite book |last=Cohen |first=Stephen F. |date=2019 |title=War with Russia? |url=|publisher=  Skyhorse Publishing, Inc. |page=190 |isbn=  978-1-5107-4581-0 }}</ref>\n\nMike Lofgren has claimed the military-industrial complex is the private part of the deep state.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mikelofgren.net/how-the-powers-that-be-maintain-the-deep-state/|title=\"Deep State\" Truthout Interview|date=February 22, 2016|access-date=August 9, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> However, [[Marc Ambinder]] has suggested that a myth about the \"deep state\" is that it functions as one entity; in reality, he states, \"the deep state contains multitudes, and they are often at odds with one another.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/five-myths-about-the-deep-state/2017/03/10/ddb09b54-04da-11e7-ad5b-d22680e18d10_story.html|title=Five myths about the deep state|last=Ambinder|first=Marc|date=March 10, 2017|work=The Washington Post|access-date=August 9, 2017|last2=Ambinder|first2=Marc|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref>\n\n[[Tufts University]] professor [[Michael J. Glennon]] claimed that President [[Barack Obama]] did not succeed in resisting and/or changing what he calls the \"double government\": the defense and national security network.<ref>{{Cite news|author=Smith, Jordan Michael|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/ideas/2014/10/18/vote-all-you-want-the-secret-government-won-change/jVSkXrENQlu8vNcBfMn9sL/story.html|title=Vote all you want. The secret government won't change.| newspaper=[[Boston Globe]]|date=October 18, 2014|access-date=August 22, 2017}}</ref> Mike Lofgren felt Obama was pushed into the [[War in Afghanistan (2001\u2013present)#2009 Increase in U.S. troops|Afghanistan \"surge\" in 2009]].<ref name=\"Lofgren_2/21/2014\"/> Another major campaign promise Obama made was the closure of [[Guantanamo Bay detention camp|Guantanamo Bay Prison Camp]], which he was unable to accomplish. This has been attributed indirectly to the influence of a deep state.<ref name=\"Time\" />\n\nPresident Donald Trump's supporters use the term to refer to allegations that intelligence officers and [[United States Executive Branch|executive branch]] officials guide policy through [[news leak|leaking]] or other internal means.<ref name=\"WaPo Ishaan\">{{Cite news |title=Is Trump fighting the deep state or creating his own? |author=Tharoor, Ishaan |date=February 1, 2017 |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/worldviews/wp/2017/02/01/is-trump-fighting-the-deep-state-or-creating-his-own/ }}</ref><ref name=\"NY Times\" /> According to a July 2017 report by the [[United States Senate Committee on Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs]], \"the Trump administration was being hit by national security leaks 'on a nearly daily basis' and at a far higher rate than its predecessors encountered\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Crowley|first=Michael|url=http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2017/09/05/deep-state-real-cia-fbi-intelligence-215537|title=The Deep State Is Real|website=[[Politico Magazine]]|date=September\u2013October 2017|accessdate=September 5, 2017}}</ref>\n\nTrump and [[Steve Bannon]], his former chief strategist, have both made allegations about a deep state which they believe is interfering with the president's agenda.<ref name=\"Times Bannon\">{{Cite news |title=Rumblings of a 'Deep State' Undermining Trump? It Was Once a Foreign Concept |author= Davis, Julie Hirschfeld |date=March 6, 2017 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/06/us/politics/deep-state-trump.html }}</ref><ref name=\"WaPo Bannon\">{{Cite news |title=Inside Trump's fury: The president rages at leaks, setbacks and accusations |author=Rucker, Phillip; Costa, Robert; and Parker, Ashley|date=March 5, 2017 |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/inside-trumps-fury-the-president-rages-at-leaks-setbacks-and-accusations/2017/03/05/40713af4-01df-11e7-ad5b-d22680e18d10_story.html }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Winter|first1=Jana|last2=Groll|first2=Elias|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2017/08/10/heres-the-memo-that-blew-up-the-nsc/|title=Here's the Memo That Blew Up the NSC|website=[[Foreign Policy]]|date=August 10, 2017|accessdate=August 15, 2017}}</ref> In 2018, describing the deep state as an \"entrenched bureaucracy\", Trump accused the [[United States Department of Justice]] \"of being part of the 'deep state{{'\"}} in a statement advocating the prosecution of [[Huma Abedin]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lucey|first1=Catherine|last2=Superville|first2=Darlene|url=https://apnews.com/8720fde079e84237b8e6cca4219aafb2/Trump-accuses-DOJ-of-being-part-of-'deep-state'|title=Trump accuses DOJ of being part of 'deep state'|website=[[Associated Press]]|date=January 2, 2018|accessdate=January 2, 2018}}</ref> Some Trump allies and right-wing media outlets have alleged that former president Barack Obama is coordinating a deep state resistance to Trump.<ref name=\"Times Bannon\" /><ref name=\"Wapo Obama\">{{Cite news |title=Trump and Republicans see a 'deep state' foe: Barack Obama |author= Weigel, David|date=March 7, 2017 |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/powerpost/wp/2017/03/07/trump-and-republicans-see-a-deep-state-foe-barack-obama/ }}</ref> While the belief in a deep state is popular among Trump supporters, critics maintain that it has no basis in reality,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://thehill.com/homenews/administration/336178-the-memo-is-trump-a-victim-of-the-deep-state|title=THE MEMO: Is Trump a victim of the 'deep state'?|newspaper=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]|date=June 5, 2017|first=Niall|last=Stanage}}</ref> arguing that the sources of the leaks frustrating the Trump administration lack the organizational depth of deep states in other countries. Critics also warned that use of the term in the U.S. could undermine confidence in vital institutions and be used to justify suppressing dissent.<ref name=\"Times Bannon\" /><ref name=\"Atlantic dangerous\">{{Cite news |title=Why it's dangerous to talk about a deep state |author=Graham, David A.|date=February 20, 2017 |newspaper=[[The Atlantic Monthly]]|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2017/02/why-its-dangerous-to-talk-about-a-deep-state/517221/ }}</ref>\n\n''[[The Washington Post]]'''s long-time conservative columnist, [[Charles Krauthammer]] said of the belief in a Deep State:\n\n<blockquote>I don\u2019t believe in the tooth fairy, the [[Knights Templar]], [[Bilderberg Group|Bilderberg]], the [[Protocols of the Elders of Zion]], a vast right wing conspiracy, or, for that matter, a vast left wing conspiracy. Are there in the U.S. government individual bureaucrats that are Democratic holdovers that would love nothing more than to damage Trump? Yeah, of course there are. Is there a concealed web of conspirators, malevolent permanent hidden shadow government? Rubbish. And I would add that Lee Harvey Oswald acted alone without the help of Ted Cruz\u2019s father.<ref name=stone /></blockquote>\n\n''[[Rolling Stone]]'' magazine, which reported Krauthammer's comment, summarizes the Deep State concept this way: \"Is there actually a deep state? If you mean entrenched bureaucracy, then of course there is. If you mean a government-wide conspiracy, then the answer is almost certainly no.\"<ref name=stone /> ''[[Salon (magazine)|Salon]]'' magazine traces Donald Trump's belief in a Deep State to [[conspiracy theorist]] [[Alex Jones]] of ''[[Infowars]]'', who, it says, \"believes that the government \u2014 aka the \"deep state\" \u2014 has orchestrated attacks and events throughout history. This includes the [[Oklahoma City bombing|bombing of the Oklahoma City federal building]], the [[Sandy Hook Elementary School shooting|massacre at Sandy Hook]] (he claims that many of the parents were actors), the [[Boston Marathon bombing|Boston Marathon attack]], and on and on,\" including believing that the [[9/11 conspiracy theories|9/11 attack]] was \"executed by the United States government.\" The magazine also points to Trump's long-time ally, [[Roger Stone]], as an influence. Stone has written several books which center on conspiracy theories, and blames [[Lyndon B. Johnson|Lyndon Johnson]] for the death of President [[John F. Kennedy]], and that Ted Cruz's father was involved in that assassination.<ref name=salon />\n\nIn an article for ''[[The New York Review of Books]]'', [[Michael Tomasky]] quoted [[Newt Gingrich]] as using the term in the context of the [[Robert Mueller]] investigation in July 2018, quoting Gingrich stating: \"[Mueller is] ... the tip of the deep state spear aimed at destroying or at a minimum undermining and crippling the Trump presidency\".<ref name=\"auto\">''The New York Review of Books'', Michael Tomalsky, August 16, 2018. Page 8.</ref> Gingrich then added to the statement that: \"The brazen redefinition of Mueller's task tells you how arrogant the deep state is and how confident it is it can get away with anything\".<ref name=\"auto\" />\n\nProfessor of international relations at Harvard University, [[Stephen Walt]], has written: \"There's no secret conspiracy or deep state running U.S. foreign policy; to the extent that there is a bipartisan foreign-policy elite, it is hiding in plain sight.\"<ref name=\"Walt_9/7/2018\">{{cite web | last=Walt | first=Stephen M. | title=The Battle for Crazytown | website=[[Foreign Policy]] | date=September 7, 2018 |url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2018/09/07/the-battle-for-crazytown/ | access-date=October 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe term has also been used in comments on the \"deep state\"-like influence allegedly wielded by career military officers such as [[H. R. McMaster]], [[John F. Kelly|John Kelly]] and [[James Mattis]] in the Trump administration. The anthropologist C. August Elliott described this state of affairs as the emergence of a 'shallow state': \"an America where public servants now function as tugboats guiding the President's very leaky ship through the shallows and away from a potential shipwreck\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Elliott |first1=C. August |title=MOABs win battles but they don't win wars |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-04-15/moabs-win-battles-but-they-dont-win-wars/8445710 |website=ABC News |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation}}</ref>\n\nOn September 5, 2018, ''[[The New York Times]]'' published an anonymous op-ed titled \"[[I Am Part of the Resistance Inside the Trump Administration]]\" written by a \"senior official in the Trump Administration\". In the essay, the official was critical of President Trump and claimed \"that many of the senior officials in [Trump's] own administration are working diligently from within to frustrate parts of his agenda and his worst inclinations\".<ref>{{cite news |author1=Anonymous |title=I Am Part of the Resistance Inside the Trump Administration |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/05/opinion/trump-white-house-anonymous-resistance.html |newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=November 17, 2018 |date=September 5, 2018}}</ref> [[House Majority Leader]] [[Kevin McCarthy (California politician)|Kevin McCarthy]] described this as evidence of the deep state at work,<ref>{{cite news |last1=McCarthy |first1=Kevin |title=A Top Republican Fires Back at 'Anonymous' |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/07/opinion/letters/kevin-mccarthy-trump-anonymous.html |website=The New York Times |accessdate=November 17, 2018 |date=September 7, 2018}}</ref> and [[David Bossie]] wrote an op-ed at Fox News claiming this was the deep state \"working against the will of the American people\".<ref name=\"7 September 2018\">{{cite web |last1=Bossie |first1=David N. |title=Anonymous NY Times op-ed shows Deep State thugs are working against the will of the American people|url=https://www.foxnews.com/opinion/anonymous-ny-times-op-ed-shows-deep-state-thugs-are-working-against-the-will-of-the-american-people.amp |newspaper=[[Fox News]] |accessdate=November 17, 2018}}</ref> However, there was some doubt as to the actual importance of the anonymous author with some estimating hundreds or thousands of possible positions could be considered \"senior officials\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Concha |first1=Joe |title='Senior' official doesn't mean anonymous NYT writer is close to Trump |url=https://thehill.com/opinion/white-house/405323-senior-official-doesnt-mean-anonymous-nyt-writer-is-close-to-trump?amp |website=The Hill |accessdate=November 17, 2018 |date=September 6, 2018}}</ref> and the inherent paradox of exposing the existence of such a group.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chait |first1=Jonathan |title=Senior White House Official Confesses Anti-Trump Cabal in Newspaper Trump Reads |url=http://nymag.com/intelligencer/amp/2018/09/senior-white-house-official-confesses-anti-trump-cabal.html |website=Intelligencer |accessdate= November 17, 2018 |date=September 5, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Polls ==\nAccording to a poll of Americans in April 2017, about half (48%) thought there was a \"deep state\", defined as \"military, intelligence and government officials who try to secretly manipulate government\", while about a third (35%) of all participants thought it was a conspiracy theory and the remainder (17%) had no opinion. Of those who believe a \"deep state\" exists, more than half (58%) said it was a major problem, a net of 28% of those surveyed.<ref name=\"ABC_47032061\">{{cite news|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/lies-damn-lies-deep-state-plenty-americans-poll/story?id=47032061|title=Nearly half of Americans think there's a 'deep state' in US: Poll|author= Staff|date=April 27, 2017|newspaper=[[ABC News]]|access-date=March 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.langerresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/1186a4DeepStateFakeNews.pdf|title=Lies, Damn Lies and the Deep State: Plenty of Americans See Them All|author=Langer Research Associates|publisher=[[ABC News]]}}</ref>\n\nA March 2018 poll found most respondents (63%) were unfamiliar with the term \"deep state\", but a majority believe that a deep state likely exists in the United States when described as \"a group of unelected government and military officials who secretly manipulate or direct national policy\". Three-fourths (74%) of the respondents say that they believe this type of group definitely (27%) or probably (47%) exists in the federal government.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/03/19/politics/americans-skeptical-government-poll/index.html|title=Americans skeptical of government, more politically engaged, poll finds|author=Wright, avid|newspaper=[[CNN]]|access-date=March 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Morin, Rebecca|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/03/19/poll-deep-state-470282||title=Poll: Majority believe 'deep state' manipulates U.S. policies|newspaper=[[Politico]]|access-date=March 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Staff|url=https://www.monmouth.edu/polling-institute/reports/monmouthpoll_us_031918|title=Public Troubled by 'Deep State'|work=[[Monmouth University Polling Institute]]|access-date=March 23, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAn October 2019 [[The Economist]]/[[YouGov]] poll found that, without giving a definition of \"deep state\" to respondents, 70% of Republicans, 38% of independents, and 13% of Democrats agreed that a \"deep state\" was \"trying to overthrow Trump.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://today.yougov.com/topics/politics/articles-reports/2019/10/16/americans-favor-impeachment-want-trump-removed|title=Americans who favor impeachment want President Trump removed, too {{!}} YouGov|last=Frankovic|first=Kathy|website=today.yougov.com|language=en-us|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref>\n\n==Closely related concepts==\nBob Jessop, in his book ''The State: Past, Present, Future'',<ref name=\"Jessop\"/> notes the similarity of three constructs:\n# 'Deep state' \u2013 for which he cites Mike Lofgren's 2014 definition: \"a hybrid association of elements of government and parts of top-level finance and industry that is effectively able to govern&nbsp;... without reference to the consent of the governed as expressed through the formal political process\".<ref name=\"Lofgren_2/21/2014\"/>\n# 'Dark state' \u2013 \"networks of officials, private firms, media outlets, think tanks, foundations, NGOs, interest groups, and other forces that attend to the needs of capital, not of everyday life\" while \"concealed from public gaze\" (or \"hidden in plain sight\"), citing Jason Lindsay (2013).{{verify quote|date=February 2019}}<ref name=Lindsey/>{{rp|37\u201338}}\n# '[[Fourth branch of government|The Fourth Branch]]' of US government \u2013 consisting of \"an ever more unchecked and unaccountable centre&nbsp;..., working behind a veil of secrecy\", citing Tom Engelhardt (2014).<ref>{{cite book | first= Tom | last=Engelhardt | title = Shadow Government: Surveillance, Secret Wars, and a Global Security State in a Single Superpower World | date=2014 | publisher= Haymarket Books | location=Chicago | isbn=9781608464272}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{col-begin|width=60%}}{{col-break}}\n* [[Bureaucracy]]\n* [[Bureaucrat]]\n* [[Council for National Policy]]\n* [[Coup d'\u00e9tat]]\n* [[Deep state in Turkey]]\n* [[Fourth branch of government]]\n* [[Groundswell group]]\n* [[Iron triangle (US politics)]]\n{{col-break}}\n* \"[[I Am Part of the Resistance Inside the Trump Administration]]\"\n* [[Military\u2013industrial complex]]\n* [[National security|National security state]]\n* [[QAnon]]\n* [[Shadow government (conspiracy)]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{cite book|author=James B. Stewart |authorlink=James B. Stewart |title=Deep State: Trump, the FBI, and the Rule of Law |publisher=[[Penguin Press]] |year=2019 |isbn=978-0525559108 |url=}}\n\n[[Category:Conspiracy theories in the United States]]\n[[Category:Conspiracy theories promoted by Donald Trump]]\n[[Category:Corruption in the United States]]\n[[Category:Deep politics]]\n[[Category:Political terminology of the United States]]\n[[Category:Political geography]]\n[[Category:Politics of the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Vanisaac", "label": "safe", "comment": "Correcting spelling: aka->a.k.a.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deep_state_in_the_United_States"}
